{
  "texts": [
    "Most of these codes satisfy Lemma 4 with i = g = 2 and j = h = 3.",
    "The exception is the [[90, 8, 10]] code, for which we can take i = 2, g = 1 and j = h = 3.However, we also note two interesting cases.",
    "First, there are codes with connected Tanner graphs that do not satisfy the conditions for a toric layout given in Lemma 4.",
    "One example of such a code is QC(A, B) with ℓ, m = 28, 14, A = x 26 + y 6 + y 8 and B = y 7 + x 9 + x 20 that has parameters [[784, 24, ≤24]].",
    "Second, for a code satisfying the conditions of Lemma 4, it need not be the case that the set A A B B {ord(), ord()} i j T g h T and the set {ℓ, m} are equal."
  ]
}